premise_source_doc_sentence: Like a page layout program , Taste also allowed the user to add these boxes if needed , as well as adjust the distance between characters  (  kerning  )  or between lines in a paragraph .
There was no need , as in a typical page layout program , to create a box to hold the text , or manually add pages or link columns as the document grew .
Taste is a Macintosh word processor that combined a number of basic features from page layout software , just a `` taste '' of it , to build a unique solution to preparing documents .
In many ways Apple 's recent Pages application shares the basic `` idea '' of Taste , combining word processing with page layout .
